    "content": "<ComponentPreview name=\"pixel-icon-demo\" />\n\nThe Icon component creates customizable, interactive pixel-based icons. It supports hover effects, color changes, and pixel shape customization.\n\n## Installation\n\n<Tabs defaultValue=\"cli\">\n\n<TabsList>\n  <TabsTrigger value=\"cli\">CLI</TabsTrigger>\n  <TabsTrigger value=\"manual\">Manual</TabsTrigger>\n</TabsList>\n<TabsContent value=\"cli\">\n\n```bash\nnpx shadcn@latest add \"https://bucharitesh.in/r/pixel-icon\"\n```\n\n</TabsContent>\n\n<TabsContent value=\"manual\">\n\n<Steps>\n\n<Step>Copy and paste the following code into your project.</Step>\n\n<ComponentSource name=\"pixel-icon\" />\n\n<Step>Copy the css and name it book.style.css</Step>\n\n{/* <ComponentCSS name=\"book.style.css\" /> */}\n\n<Step>Update the import paths to match your project setup.</Step>\n\n</Steps>\n\n</TabsContent>\n\n</Tabs>\n\n## Props\n\n| Prop           | Type                    | Description                                          | Default     |\n|----------------|-------------------------|------------------------------------------------------|-------------|\n| icon           | number[][]              | 2D array representing the icon's pixel layout        | (Required)  |\n| baseColor      | string                  | Base color of the icon                               | (Required)  |\n| flickerColor   | string                  | Color used for the flicker effect                    | (Required)  |\n| secondaryColor | string                  | Secondary color for additional details               | \"gray\"      |\n| size           | number                  | Size of the icon in pixels                           | 80          |\n| flickerChance  | number                  | Probability of pixel color change on hover (0 to 1)  | 0.3         |\n| pixelShape     | \"circle\" \\| \"square\"    | Shape of individual pixels                           | \"circle\"    |\n| className      | string                  | Additional CSS classes for the icon container        |             |\n\n## Usage\n\n```jsx\nimport PixelIcon from './PixelIcon'\n\nconst MyComponent = () => {\n  const iconData = [\n    [1, 1, 1],\n    [1, 0, 1],\n    [1, 1, 1],\n  ]\n\n  return (\n    <PixelIcon\n      icon={iconData}\n      baseColor=\"#ff0000\"\n      flickerColor=\"#ffff00\"\n      secondaryColor=\"#0000ff\"\n      size={100}\n      flickerChance={0.5}\n      pixelShape=\"square\"\n    />\n  )\n}\n```\n\n## Features\n\n- **Interactive Hover Effect**: The icon's pixels flicker and change colors when hovered over.\n- **Customizable Colors**: Set base, flicker, and secondary colors to match your design.\n- **Adjustable Size**: Easily change the icon's size to fit your layout.\n- **Pixel Shape Options**: Choose between circular or square pixels.\n- **Performance Optimized**: Uses `requestAnimationFrame` for smooth animations.\n- **Responsive**: Adapts to different screen resolutions using `devicePixelRatio`.\n\n## Accessibility\n\nThe component includes appropriate ARIA attributes for better accessibility:\n\n- `role=\"img\"` on the container div\n- `aria-label=\"Pixel icon\"` for screen readers\n- `aria-hidden=\"true\"` on the canvas element\n\n## Credits\n\n- Credit to [@rauno](https://rauno.me/craft/vercel#pixelated-iconography) for this beautiful blog :)",
